# Payload basics

Use **[official docs](https://payloadcms.com/docs/)** as source of truth (mirrored from [`payloadcms/payload` docs](https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/tree/main/docs)). Prefer **schema → Local API → UI**, not the reverse.

## Discovering documentation (humans, agents, crawlers)

- **Site & navigation:** Use the [docs](https://payloadcms.com/docs/) sidebar and search; this repo’s **documentation reference map** (below) and **`payload-features-overview.mdc`** map areas → rules.
- **Machine-friendly doc lists:** The marketing site may publish **[`/docs/llms.txt`](https://payloadcms.com/docs/llms.txt)** (same pattern as many Vercel doc sites — a compact index of doc URLs). If that URL is unavailable, use the **[GitHub `docs/` tree](https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/tree/main/docs)** or **`pnpm generate:llms`** in this repo to refresh committed `public/llms.txt` / `public/llms-full.txt` from GitHub (**`payload-deployment.mdc`**).
- **Full-site sitemaps:** **[payloadcms.com/sitemap.xml](https://payloadcms.com/sitemap.xml)** is usually a **sitemap index** that points at split files (e.g. **`sitemap-0.xml`**, **`sitemap-1.xml`**, …) listing **every** crawlable URL — blog, marketing, case studies, **and** `/docs/...` — so it is **large and mixed-scope**. Prefer **`llms.txt`** (when present) or the **hub rules** for docs-shaped work; use the sitemap when you need **complete** domain coverage or audit crawls.
- **Markdown:** Official pages sometimes offer **`.md`** variants or note “available as Markdown” in the page footer — same idea as Next.js docs.

**Feature hub:** `payload-features-overview.mdc` maps [custom components](https://payloadcms.com/docs/custom-components/overview), [authentication](https://payloadcms.com/docs/authentication/overview), [rich text](https://payloadcms.com/docs/rich-text/overview), [live preview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/live-preview/overview), [versions](https://payloadcms.com/docs/versions/overview), [upload](https://payloadcms.com/docs/upload/overview), [folders](https://payloadcms.com/docs/folders/overview), [email](https://payloadcms.com/docs/email/overview), [jobs queue](https://payloadcms.com/docs/jobs-queue/overview), [query presets](https://payloadcms.com/docs/query-presets/overview), [trash](https://payloadcms.com/docs/trash/overview), [troubleshooting](https://payloadcms.com/docs/troubleshooting/troubleshooting), [TypeScript](https://payloadcms.com/docs/typescript/overview), and other areas to the matching `.cursor/rules/payload-*.mdc` files.

**Ecosystem hub:** `payload-ecosystem.mdc` maps [plugins overview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/plugins/overview), [ecommerce overview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/ecommerce/overview), [examples overview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/examples/overview), and [Vercel Content Link](https://payloadcms.com/docs/integrations/vercel-content-link) to the matching rules (`payload-plugins`, `payload-ecommerce`, `payload-examples`, `payload-docs-support`).

**Deployment hub:** `payload-deployment.mdc` maps [building without a database connection](https://payloadcms.com/docs/production/building-without-a-db-connection), [deployment](https://payloadcms.com/docs/production/deployment), [preventing abuse](https://payloadcms.com/docs/production/preventing-abuse), and [performance overview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/performance/overview) to `payload-deployment` (build/CI entry), `payload-security-deployment`, and `payload-performance`.

**Next.js (companion stack):** **`next-basics.mdc`** (always-on) and **`next-features-overview.mdc`** (hub) map [nextjs.org/docs](https://nextjs.org/docs/) to **`next-*.mdc`** topic rules. **Payload still leads**; canonical **boundary** and **`getPayload`/depth** stay in **§ Payload vs Next.js** and **When changing behavior** below.

**Rules discipline:** hubs above **link** to one topic rule each—do not paste duplicate doc tables or long prose into multiple `.mdc` files. TS naming + generated-type workflow → **`payload-typescript.mdc`** only.

**Reading discipline:** follow **`agent-read-rules.mdc`** — route via this file, read **only** applicable topic rules **in full**, batched in parallel when possible.

## Payload vs Next.js (boundary)

**→ Next.js when Payload is not enough:** Payload covers **schema, access, hooks, Local API, admin UI, versions/uploads/plugins**. What fits poorly there — **Middleware**, **Route Handlers** (`src/app/api/**`), **`draftMode` / `headers()` / `cookies()`**, **App Router caching** (`unstable_cache`, `revalidateTag`, ISR), **streaming**, **redirects** outside the redirects plugin, **image/font optimization**, **edge-only** behavior — belongs in **Next.js** (`src/app`, `middleware.ts`). Still **read/write CMS data via `getPayload`** from RSC and handlers; Next owns **request lifecycle and delivery**, not a duplicate editorial source.

**→ Payload when Next.js is not enough:** Do not treat Next as the CMS. **Authorable content**, **structured fields**, **relationships**, **uploads**, **drafts/versions**, **role-based access**, **validation on save**, **admin workflows**, and anything that should **migrate with the DB** belong in **Payload** (collections/globals/blocks/plugins). Avoid hard-coding copy or page structure in React when editors should own it; avoid ad hoc JSON files or env-only “content” for what should be queryable and permissioned like other documents.

## When changing behavior

1. **Collections / globals / fields / plugins** — prefer **`src/plugins/schema`** (and `getSchemaPlugins` order in `src/plugins/index.ts`) when wiring is **shared or template-scoped**; otherwise edit **`src/collections`**, **`src/globals`**, **`src/fields`**, **`src/blocks`**; adjust `access` and `hooks` per docs (`payload-plugins.mdc`).
2. **Regenerate** — `pnpm generate:types` (and `pnpm generate:importmap` if admin imports/custom components changed).
3. **Database** — adapter/migrations follow [Database overview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/database/overview); prod deploy uses project scripts (see `package.json`).
4. **Consumers** — Next server: `@root/lib/getPayload`; scripts/CLI: `getPayload({ config })` + `@payload-config`. `src/migrate.ts` (Slate → Lexical) also uses `@root/lib/getPayload`. Match **`depth`** to what the UI needs; cache keys must include **`depth`** when using `unstable_cache` around `find` (see `utilities/getDocument.ts`).

